cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing techniques to identify sound concepts and relations in text.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on acoustic concepts and scenes.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be a possible category as the paper discusses the use of large scale text corpora to generate sound concepts.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses LSTM recurrent neural network for predicting sound concepts.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a possible category as the paper deals with identifying and extracting relevant information from text.
